	<div style="position: relative; top: 6px; left:5px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 13px; padding-left: 45px;">Why non-premium users should run Magelo Update, too...</div>	
	<div style="position: relative; top: 6px; left:10px;">
		<img class="png32" style="position: absolute; top:0px; left:0px;" src="/images/shared/right_menu/support_icone_off.png" width="33" height="15">
		<img class="png32" style="position: absolute;top:-17px; left:4px;" src="/images/localized/picto/faq_icone.png" width="24" height="24">
	</div>
	<hr class="line">
	<br>
	
	
	<div>Non-premium Magelo users have a number of good reasons to run <a href='http://eq.magelo.com/magelo_update.jspa' target='new'>Magelo Update</a>, even though their Synchronize Profile feature is disabled.<br/>
<br/>
1. The Magelo Update program is the sole means of adding items to our database and keeping them up to date. Any user may be the one that contributes an important entry or update, which allows everyone to use the up to date item in their profiles.<br/>
<br/>
<em class="emphasis">Magelo staff cannot and will not manually access the global item database to alter or insert items. Not only is this prone to human error, but items have a number of hidden attributes (like level of effect and item ID number, but there&#039;s more) that players have no knowledge of.</em><br/>
<br/>
2. Magelo Update will automatically detect your in game character as soon as you run it. The character with its identity card (vital information, guild status, ranking status) will be built in real time and visible in &quot;My characters&quot; on the website.<br/>
<br/>
3. By running Magelo Update while logged into the game you verify for us that your character exists on the specified server, which is proof enough to include your manually updated profile in Magelo&#039;s ranking system. Without doing this step the profile is excluded. This requirement helps prevent abuse of the ranking system.<br/>
<br/>
4. Your character&#039;s guild tag will not appear on his or her manually updated Magelo profile until you run Magelo Update while the character is logged into the game. The program confirms the guild tag in-game then updates the character&#039;s entry in our database. This is done to prevent abuse of the guild tagging feature.<br/>
<br/>
5. Magelo Update can save a report of your items, skills, etc. to a local text file for you to use as you see fit, one per character &quot;seen&quot; by the program during a game session.<br/>
<br/>
<em class="emphasis">Written initially by <a href='http://www.valoran.net/' target='new'>Onetree</a>, updated July 8, 2007 by Onetree</em></div>
